From: Akhil P Oommen <akhilpo@oss.qualcomm.com>
drm/msm: Adreno 830 (gen8_0_0) GPU driver support for SM8750 / Odin 3

The GPU-driver half of ROCKNIX's 0000_to_0025 qcom-adreno waiting-for-upstream
bundle, rebased onto armada's 7.0.11 series. armada already carries the bundle's
clk/qcom slice (sm8750-gpucc-clock-controller.patch), its sm8750.dtsi GPU nodes
(sm8750-add-display-gpu-nodes.patch), and the a740 IFPC hunk (0004); this adds
only the remaining drivers/gpu/drm/msm/* delta — the a830 (ADRENO_8XX_GEN1)
catalog entry, reglists, gen80000 firmware names, a8xx gen1 bringup, and GMU/HFI
support. Without it the msm driver has no a830 chip-id → the Odin 3 GPU never
probes (display works; gamescope/Vulkan fails). Firmware (gen80000_*) already
ships via qcom-firmware.

